This paper deals with training low-precision convolutional neural networks, which is a topic closely related to computer vision (cs.CV). Additionally, the paper proposes novel optimization strategies and learning schemes, which are relevant to machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the impact of low-precision networks on accuracy, which is a topic related to neural networks (cs.NE). Finally, the paper presents experimental results on image datasets, which is a topic related to multimedia (cs.MM).
